000100 IDENTIFICATION DIVISION. 
000200 PROGRAM-ID. files.
000300 AUTHOR. LodoreStiffler.
000400* This program demonstrates how to read from and write to a file in COBOL.
000401*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
000410 ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
000411*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
000420 INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
000430 FILE-CONTROL.
000440     SELECT ACCT-FILE ASSIGN TO "accounts.dat"
000450         ORGANIZATION IS SEQUENTIAL
000451*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
000460 DATA DIVISION.
000461*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
000470 FILE SECTION.
000480 FD ACCT-FILE.
000490 01 ACCT-RECORD.
000500     05 ACCT-NOM PIC X(25).
000510     05 ACCT-BAL PIC 9(7)V99.
000520     05 FIRST-NAME PIC X(15).
000530     05 LAST-NAME PIC X(15).
000540     05 COMMENTS PIC X(50).
000541*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
000550 WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
000551*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
000560 01 WS-EOF PIC X VALUE "N".
000570*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
000580 PROCEDURE DIVISION.
000581*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
000590     OPEN OUTPUT ACCT-FILE.
000600     MOVE "JD32148" TO ACCT-NOM.
000610     MOVE 12345.67 TO ACCT-BAL.
000620     MOVE "John" TO FIRST-NAME.
000630     MOVE "Doe" TO LAST-NAME.
000640     MOVE "This is a comment." TO COMMENTS.
000650     WRITE ACCT-RECORD.
000660     CLOSE ACCT-FILE.
000670* Now read the record back from the file
000680     OPEN INPUT ACCT-FILE.
000690     PERFORM UNTIL WS-EOF = "Y"
000700         READ ACCT-FILE INTO ACCT-RECORD
000710             AT END
000720                 MOVE "Y" TO WS-EOF
000730             NOT AT END
000740                 DISPLAY "Account Number: " ACCT-NOM
000750                 DISPLAY "Account Balance: " ACCT-BAL
000760                 DISPLAY "First Name: " FIRST-NAME
000770                 DISPLAY "Last Name: " LAST-NAME
000780                 DISPLAY "Comments: " COMMENTS
000790         END-READ
000800     END-PERFORM.
000810     CLOSE ACCT-FILE.
000820     STOP RUN.